[SN]TITLE[SN]
Stainby Quarry death: Family tribute to Richard Marjoram

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The family of a man who died after an incident at a quarry have paid tribute to a "special husband, fantastic father and much loved grandfather".

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Richard Marjoram, 57, from Deeping St Nicholas, died following an "industrial accident" involving an HGV at Stainby Quarry, near Grantham.
Police were called to the quarry at about 11:00 BST on Monday.
Lincolnshire Police said it is investigating the incident together with the Health and Safety Executive.
